<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="tie-vt">tie <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /taɪ/    美 /taɪ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(用带、绳、线等) 系；拴；扎：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Tie</strong> your bike to a tree so as to prevent it from being stolen<strong>to_1</strong>
把自行车拴在树上以防被偷。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="tie-up">tie up</h3>
<p>1.<strong>系紧；拴牢：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Susan handed him the string so he could tie up the box.
苏珊把绳子递给他，让他能绑好盒子。</p><footer>人教⑨ – 4</footer></div></div>